info.name: DAW-Gomoku
info.description:
# API for Gomoku Game

_**Gomoku**_, also called _Five in a Row_, is an abstract strategy board game. It is traditionally played with black and white stones on a 15×15 board while in the past a 19×19 board was standard.

## To use our API

The app is made of various resources, some need authorization (header Authorization with Bearer {token}.

**Requests that don't need authorization:**

| Resource | Method | URI | More Info |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Home | GET | http://{server}:8080/api | current page |
| System Info | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/info | Siren entities description |
| API examples | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/examples | usage examples |
| About | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/about | Version and authors info |
| Gomoku Rules | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/rules |  |
| Rankings | GET | http://{server}:8080/ranks | user stats and rankings |
| Create user | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/users | needs JSON body with parameters username and password |

**Requests that require authorization:**

| Resource | Method | URI | More Info |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Login | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/token | Redirects to user home |
| User home | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/me | User stats and rank, could change password |
| Logout | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/logout |  |
| Show games in lobby | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/lobby | Games by type and opponent rank in the lobby |
| Add game to lobby | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/lobby | needs JSON body with parameters |
| Check game in lobby status | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/lcheckmatch |  |
| Delete game from lobby | DEL | http://{server}:8080/api/lobby/{id} | Give-up / remove game from lobby |
| Join as opponent to game in lobby | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/joingame | needs JSON body with the lobby game id |
| View game | GET | http://{server}:8080/api/game |  |
| Play turn | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/game | needs JSON body with the x and y coordinates of the board |
| Give up from game | POST | http://{server}:8080/api/giveup |  |

**To play a game:**

- Create user
- Login
- List or create a game in lobby
- Check when game has an opponent
- Play a turn
    

# **Rules**

---

Specific rules aplied in some variants

- Swap after 1st move
- Three and three
- Four and four
- Overlines
- Capture
    

**Swap after 1st move**

Once the first player places a black stone on the board, the second player has the right to swap colors.

**Three and three**

Bans a move that simultaneously forms two open rows of three stones (rows not blocked by an opponent's stone at either end).

**Four and four**

Bans a move that simultaneously forms two rows of four stones (open or not).

**Overlines**

Prevent a player from winning if they form a line of six or more stones.

**Capture**

A pair of stones of the same color may be captured by the opponent by means of custodial capture (sandwiching a line of two stones lengthwise).

## **Variants**

---

- Freestyle
- Freestyle 2 (swap after 1st move)
- Renju (only 15x15 board)
- Caro
- Omok (only 19x19 board)
- Pente
    

**Freestyle**

Has no restrictions on either player and allows a player to win by creating a line of five or more stones, with each player alternating turns placing one stone at a time.

**Freestyle 2 (Swap after 1st move)**

Uses the "swap after 1st move" rule. The rest of the game proceeds as freestyle.

**Renju**

Is played on a 15×15 board, with the rules of three and three, four and four, and overlines applied to Black only.

**Caro**

The winner must have an overline or an unbroken row of five stones that is not blocked at either end (overlines are immune to this rule).

**Omok**

Similar to Freestyle gomoku; however, it is played on a 19×19 board and includes the rule of _three and three._

**Ninuki-renju**

Also called Wu, Ninuki Renju is a variant which adds capturing to the game. The winner is the player either to make a perfect five in a row, or to capture five pairs of the opponent's stones. It uses a 15x15 board and the rules of three and three and overlines. It also allows the game to continue after a player has formed a row of five stones if their opponent can capture a pair across the line.

**Pente**

Pente is related to Ninuki-Renju, and has the same custodial capture method, but is most often played on a 19x19 board and does not use the rules of three and three, four and four, or overlines.

## **Openings**

---

- Open (no tournment opening)
- Swap
- Swap 2
- Pro
- Long Pro
- Soosõrv (aplied only to Renju variant)
    

**Swap**

The tentative first player places three stones (two black, and one white) anywhere on the board. The tentative second player then chooses which color to play as. Play proceeds from there as normal with white playing their second stone.

**Swap 2**

The tentative first player places three stones on the board, two black and one white. The tentative second player then has three options:

1. They can choose to play as white and place a second white stone
2. They can swap their color and choose to play as black
3. Or they can place two more stones, one black and one white, and pass the choice of which color to play back to the tentative first player.
    

**Pro**

The first player's first stone must be placed in the center of the board. The second player's first stone may be placed anywhere on the board. The first player's second stone must be placed at least three intersections away from the first stone (two empty intersections in between the two stones).

**Long Pro**

The first player's first stone must be placed in the center of the board. The second player's first stone may be placed anywhere on the board. The first player's second stone must be placed at least four intersections away from the first stone (three empty intersections in between the two stones).

**Soosõrv**

The sequence of moves implied by the rule follows.

- The first player puts one of the 26 allowed openings acordingly to the restrigions bellow.
- The other player has the right to swap.
- The white player puts the 4th move anywhere on board and declares whether there will be 1, 2, 3 or 4 fifth moves offered in the game.
- The other player has a right to swap.
- The black player puts as many 5th moves on the board as it was declared before. The fifth moves can not be symmetrical.
- The white player chooses one 5th from these offerings and plays the 6th move.
    

Restrictions on first move

- The first move is black and must be played in the center of the board.
- The second move is white and must be played in the center 3x3 square.
- The third move is black and must be played in the center 5x5 square.

request.description:
To create a user.

Require body with JSON, with the fields, "username" and "password".  
Password must be at least 8 character long, have and uppercase letter, a lowercase letter, a number and a symbol.

Can return the errors:  
\- user already exists

\- insecure password

item.description: Request that don't need bearer token

item.name: Auth token requests

request.description:
To logout the user

TODO: If the user have a game in looby, delete the game

TODO: If the user is currently playing a game, give victory by give up to the opponent

To login an existing user

Require body with fields "username" and "password"

On success returns a JSON with the field "token" to be used in subsequente requests

On failure returns the error "user or password are invalid"

item.name: Lobby

request.description:
To list all games created by other players in the lobby

TODO: for each game created in lobby, should show the game type (variant, opening and board size) and maybe the rank of the user who created the game (to prevent high ranking users to play with novices) -> Gives error creating the list

Returns a JSON body acordingly (no games in lobby or the list of game types / user rankings)

To check if the created game already have an opponent  
Response could be a redirect for the created game or a no opponent yet, ask again in x seconds

response.name: Check created game status

request.description:
To add a game to the lobby and wait for opponent  
Requires body with fields "variant", "opening" and "boardSize"

On success returns JSON with the lobby game id  
On failure returns one of the following errors:

\- invalid variant  
\- invalid openning

\- invalid boardSize

\- variant {variant} does not support openning {openning} (TODO)

\- variant {variant} does not support the chosen board size (TODO)

To delete a game created in the lobby

Automatic if user logout with a game created or if a user decides to play diffferent game

Be the opponent to a created game in the lobby

TODO: implement

request.description:
To play a game move  
Require JSON with the fields "x" and "y" that represents a coordinate in the game board starting from (0, 0) until (boardSize - 1, boardSize - 1)  
On success redirects to view game, and show victory if its the case (TODO)  
On failure return error "invalid move" (TODO)

To view the game and if its his turn to play

Returns a game representation with all the moves until the moment and the player who should make the next turn (TODO)

To give up from the game  
(Automatically the opponent wins) (TODO)
